question.title: How many US banks will fail from January through April 2026?
question.description:
A [bank failure](https://www.investopedia.com/terms/b/bank-failure.asp) occurs when a bank is unable to meet its financial obligations because it lacks sufficient assets or liquidity. In the United States, the vast majority of banks are insured by the [Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Federal_Deposit_Insurance_Corporation) (FDIC), which guarantees deposits up to \$250,000 and supervises the stability of the banking system.

Since October 1, 2000, the FDIC has comprehensively tracked failed banks under its insurance in the [FDIC Failed Bank List](https://www.fdic.gov/bank-failures/failed-bank-list). As of January 2026, 572 insured bank failures appear on the list.
question.resolution_criteria:
This question will resolve as the number of United States bank failures that occur on or after January 1, 2026, and before May 1, 2026.

The primary source for this question will be the [FDIC Failed Bank List](https://www.fdic.gov/bank-failures/failed-bank-list); however, credible sources may also be used if the FDIC's list appears to be incomplete.
question.fine_print: This question refers only to FDIC insured banks; other banks will have no impact on this question.
